tux-im (0.1.0-3) resolute; urgency=medium

  * fix(config): _merge must handle PEP 563 forward-ref annotations and
    generic container inner types.  After 0.1.0-2 the engine still
    crashed on startup because `from __future__ import annotations`
    turns every annotation into a string, so `fields[k].type` was the
    string "str" / "list[str]" and isinstance() rejected it.  Now uses
    typing.get_type_hints() to resolve annotations to real types, and
    checks container inner types (list[T].__args__[0]) explicitly.
    Adds tests/test_config.py with regression coverage.

 -- TUX IM contributors <tux-im@example.com>  Tue, 23 Jun 2026 10:42:00 +0000

tux-im (0.1.0-2) resolute; urgency=medium

  * fix(config): _merge must read field TYPES, not values.  Use
    __dataclass_fields__[k].type instead of asdict() so the runtime
    type check in Config._apply does not crash on startup with
    "TypeError: isinstance() arg 2 must be a type, ...".

 -- TUX IM contributors <tux-im@example.com>  Tue, 23 Jun 2026 10:36:00 +0000

